rComments: His style is VERYYYYYYY unstructured. We didn't get our syllabus until the 3rd class of the semester. Assignment expectations are pretty vague. BUT Kelly is very laid back and if you do the readings you will do well in the course. His lectures don't cover much of the readings so make sure you read, the exams are 100% based on reading materials.

I took a course on Municipal & Planning Law taught by Kelly Snow. Got 78%.  If you like laid back lectures, you'll love him.   I completed two assignments, and my tip is to try to 'look' as professional as possible, and you'll get good feedback.

Decent prof. A little unstructured, which was frustrating at times. He doesn't give a lot of guidance with the assignments. He wasn't very accessible - he didn't have office hours and it was hard getting him to respond to emails. But, he's a pretty generous marker. Exams were based entirely on the readings, so if you do them, it's easy to do well.

Kelly is a great guy but he is so unreliable, he will not reply to emails, he doesn't have office hours and the structure of the course is a mess. The final exam was surprising because the questions were so in depth about material he was supposed to cover but he never actually did. would not recommend if you like structured courses
Very cool and sincere.  Really interesting course.  It doesn't hurt that he's good looking... 3
